  "key_finding": "Q3 families are substrate-sensitive for two distinct reasons: (1) parametric families (z_dephasing, phase_damping, phase_flip) have a channel parameter p whose gradient path differs between float32/autograd and float64/finite-diff; (2) non-parametric families (CNOT, mutual_information) accumulate dtype precision error in complex matrix operations or near-zero eigenvalue log computations. All Q3 families are topology-insensitive because the OUTPUT STRUCTURE is fixed regardless of how the computation is wired (no graph-level ordering effect).",
